  "texts": [
    "In view of (17a), it suffices to show that every shape operator L X ∈ End(𝔫) at b satisfies the assumptions of Lemma A.8.",
    "Viewing h as a section of the flat G/K-bundle B × ρ G/K, we haveh -1 dh(X) = 2 L X.Thus, L X is both a h-self-adjoint endomorphism of adM, and tangent to the fibres of the flat G/K-bundle over B.",
    "By definition of G, this implies that L X = D + D T where D ∈ Γ Der(adM) commutes with β, and the proof is concluded.",
    "□ Definition 3.5.",
    "Two solutions (ǧ 1, ρ 1, h 1), (ǧ 2, ρ 2, h 2) of the twisted harmonic-Einstein equations for the pair (B, G/K) are called equivalent if there exists f ∈ Diff(B) and φ ∈ G such that(23) f * ǧ2 = ǧ1, C φ • ρ 1 = ρ 2 • f *, φ • h 1 = h 2 • f,where f *: π 1 (B) → π 1 (B) is the induced action on the fundamental group and C φ (q) = φqφ -1 for q ∈ G.The significance of this equivalence notion relies on the following Proposition 3.6."
